Champions Liverpool proved themselves on Saturday when they hit seven goals past Crystal Palace at Selhurst Park. The Reds, coming from a 2-1 victory against Tottenham during the week, recorded their first away win in the English Premier League. They are now six points clear at the top of the Premier League table. Minamino, Sadio Mané, Roberto Firrmino, Jordan Henderson and Mohammed Salah got their names in the score sheet. Commenting at the end of the match, Liverpool Coach, Jurgen Klopp commended his boys, saying “this is a very good match, my boys proved themselves. Goal difference, this is good for us. Crystal Palace also had their moment. “This guarantees us to be amongst the top, which gives us a good Christmas.”